Variable Purpose <code>--surface</code> Semi-transparent fill for cards, tiles, and input backgrounds <code>--surface-hover</code> Fill applied on hover — should be slightly more opaque than <code>--surface</code> <p>Use <code>rgba()</code> values so the underlying background color shows through:</p> <pre><code>--surface:       rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);
--surface-hover: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.09);
</code></pre> <p>For light themes, flip the channel:</p> <pre><code>--surface:       rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.04);
--surface-hover: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
</code></pre>

Variable Purpose <code>--border</code> Default border color for all UI elements <code>--border-focus</code> Border highlight when an input or control has focus <pre><code>/* Dark */
--border:       rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
--border-focus: rgba(120, 80, 200, 0.5);

/* Light */
--border:       rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
--border-focus: rgba(77, 111, 255, 0.45);
</code></pre>

Variable Typical use <code>--text-0</code> Primary text — headings, labels, active values <code>--text-1</code> Secondary text — descriptions, placeholders, subdued labels <code>--text-2</code> Tertiary text — timestamps, disabled states, hint text <pre><code>/* Dark */
--text-0: #ebebeb;
--text-1: #999999;
--text-2: #555555;

/* Light */
--text-0: #1a1a1c;
--text-1: #5c5c66;
--text-2: #8a8a96;
</code></pre>

Variable Purpose <code>--accent</code> Brand/highlight color — buttons, selected borders, links, toggle track <code>--accent-glow</code> Transparent version of accent used for glows and selected halos <p><code>--accent-glow</code> should be <code>rgba()</code> of <code>--accent</code> at around 15–25% opacity:</p> <pre><code>--accent:      #7aa2f7;
--accent-glow: rgba(122, 162, 247, 0.2);
</code></pre>

Variable Purpose <code>--ha-on</code> Color of HA entity state badge and preview when the entity is on <code>--ha-off</code> Color of HA entity state badge when the entity is off <p>These are used by the Home Assistant plugin's entity picker and preview panel. If you don't use HA, you can set them to <code>--success</code> and <code>--text-2</code>:</p> <pre><code>--ha-on:  var(--success);
--ha-off: var(--text-2);
</code></pre>

Variable Default Purpose <code>--radius</code> <code>10px</code> Corner radius for cards, buttons, and modals <code>--radius-sm</code> <code>6px</code> Smaller corner radius for inputs and tags <code>--font</code> <code>"Inter", system-ui, …</code> Font stack for all UI text <p>These are set in <code>style.css</code>. Override them in your theme only when you intentionally want a different shape or typeface:</p> <pre><code>:root {
    --radius:    12px;   /* rounder than default */
    --radius-sm: 8px;
    --font: "JetBrains Mono", monospace;
}
</code></pre>
